Author: Kostas Krikellas <131142368+kkrik-es@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu Oct 3 23:09:45 2024 +0300

    Use second pass for deeply nested array elements (#114060)
    
    Deeply nested array elements with ignored source need to use the second
    parsing pass, to avoid missing the source from siblings that go through
    stored source.

